Step B6 — Add 5 new sections to Tab Cycle
Now we add 5 new sections to the Cycle tab — one per stage. They'll initially be empty; we'll fill them in subsequent steps.
Add Section 1: Stage 1 — Review Changes

In the form editor, navigate to the Tab Cycle (should be selected)
Click on the canvas BELOW the Import Warnings section (or wherever you want the new section to land — at the bottom of Tab Cycle is fine)
In the toolbar at the top, click Component → look for "1-column section" or "Section"

Alternative: + Section button if visible
Alternative: drag a section component from the left rail


A new empty section appears
Click on the section header → in the right properties panel:

Display name (Label): Stage 1 — Review Changes
Name (internal): leave default or set to tab_stage_1 if asked
Layout: 1 column (default)


Press Enter / click outside

Tell me when Section "Stage 1 — Review Changes" exists at the bottom of Tab Cycle.
If the way to add a section is different from what I described, screenshot it and I'll adjust.





